titlePage.byline:
By
    F. C. Burnand, Esq.,
     (Member of the Dramatic Authors' Society), 
    Author Of
     Patient Penelope, or The Return of Ulysses Ixion, or the Man at the Wheel;
     Alonzo the Brave, or Faust and the Fair Imogene; Villikins and his Dinah; Lord Lovel and Lady Nancy Bell;
     Romance under Difficulties In for a Holiday; Dido; King of the Merrows; Deerfoot; Fair Rosamond;
     Robin Hood, or The Foresters' Fete; Acis and Galatea; The Deal Boatman;
    &c., &c.
    and part author of
     B. B.; Volunteer Ball; Turkish Bath; Carte de Visite; The Isle of St. Tropez; Easy Shaving; &c., &c.
